name: Bunbury Centrelink
directions: Toilet is always kept locked; ask a staff member for access.
comment: Manual door, but there will be a staff member opening it if you need help.  The building has security and safe waiting areas; a very safe place to be if you're facing harassment.  Not particularly cheerful, but no one will care if you hang out for an extended time.  They also have free wifi!

name: Wyalup/ Rocky Point carpark
directions: At the North end of Ocean Drive.  The toilets are the small building to the side of the carpark.
comment: Manual sliding door.  No change table, but a bench that could be used as one.  Includes a shower (cold water only) with rails and a bench.  The area is a nice park that includes beach access, covered picnic benches and free gas barbecues.  Plenty of free parking (2-hour time limit on weekdays only).

name: Nandos Bunbury
directions: Accessible toilet is hard right past a dividing wall immediately past the tables; it's easy to miss and go on to the gendered toilets (which are single occupant).
comment: Manual doors.  Accessibility probably not the best; there are narrow areas and sharp turns.  Only available during restaurant opening hours.

name: Highway Hotes
street: Intersection of Forrest Ave and Spencer St
directions: Enter hotel by main entrance and follow signs.
comment: Manual door.  The main entrance has steps and a ramp.  Ample free parking in hotel carpark, or at shopping centre across the road.  Available during opening hours, 11am-midnight.

name: Bunbury Plaza
directions: Toilets clearly signposted close to specialty shops.
comment: Manual door.  Closed between 9pm-7am.

name: The Village at Margs Shopping Centre
directions: From Bussel Hwy, turn east up Wilmott Ave at the hotel.  The Village is on the corner opposite the post office.
comment: Has an electric door and a sharps disposal.  Only available during opening hours for the shopping centre.  Ample free undercover and street parking.
